com.vectorprint.report.itext

Class VectorPrintDocument

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.itextpdf.text.Document
      • com.vectorprint.report.itext.VectorPrintDocument
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.itextpdf.text.DocListener, com.itextpdf.text.ElementListener, com.itextpdf.text.pdf.interfaces.IAccessibleElement, EventListener

    public class VectorPrintDocument
extends com.itextpdf.text.Document
    This subclass of document gathers information for table of contents and enables you to work with hooks. Hooks are added to this document before elements are added and enable for example drawing near content.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth at VectorPrint.nl

      • add

        public boolean add(com.itextpdf.text.Element element)
            throws com.itextpdf.text.DocumentException
        If there is a hook for the element it will be processed, For all hooks except stylelater StyleHelper.delayedStyle(com.itextpdf.text.Chunk, java.lang.String, java.util.Collection, com.vectorprint.report.itext.EventHelper, com.itextpdf.text.Image) (variant without image when there is none) will be called. When element is a Section the pagenumber and the Section are remembered, see getToc().
